title: For Sale:  Arsenal, Inc. SLR-107CR
postcontent:
Special Edition, Arsenal, Inc., folding-stocked, SLR-107CR, in 7.62x39 caliber. Krinkov-style flash hider makes rifle appear to be a SBR (only 25” long when folded), but it's actually a removable, threaded, shroud, covering up the end of a 16-1/4”, BATF legal, barrel. If you do decide to chop the barrel & register it as a SBR, you easily can, the gas block has already been ported properly & it has the correct length gas system. Not a cheap kit rifle. New, factory-produced in Bulgaria. Bulgarian stamped receiver with side-mounted scope rail. Bulgarian barrel, chrome lined & hammer forged. The polymer buttstock locks up solid when folded & unfolded, no wobble, & it has a cleaning kit trapdoor. Original rear sight replaced with a Mojo Micro Click rear Ghost Ring sight that is elevation & windage adjustable. It pairs up great with the gas block mounted front sight. The gas block is 24x1.5mm right-hand threaded in order to accept it's Krinkov-style threaded barrel shroud. If you decide to chop the barrel & SBR it, you can screw on any 24mm threaded flash hider out there. 
This rifle has had one thirty-round clip through it (for sighting in it's new rear ghost ring sight). 
 Included with the rifle will be the Mojo adjustable rear sight, as well as its original sight (in the box). Also included witll be its original 5-round Bulgarian waffle magazine, manual, box, cleaning kit, & cleaning rod.
*I can also remove all of the aftermarket components from the rifle, with the exception of the Mojo click-adjustable rear sight, & sell the rifle for $1060.00.
